content.raw: Just to summarize: Two versions of the docks are generated: a static and a dynamic \(floating\). The dynamic version gets loaded by adding the `_dynamic` suffix to the model name. For now, in VRX, we’re still using the more conservative approach loading the static versions.
content.html: Just to summarize: Two versions of the docks are generated: a static and a dynamic (floating). The dynamic version gets loaded by adding the _dynamic suffix to the model name. For now, in VRX, we’re still using the more conservative approach loading the static versions.
